# Test Classification Plan — `tests/main_app`

## Classification Rules

| Type | Criteria |
|------|----------|
| **unit** | Tests a single function/class in isolation; uses mocks; no real DB/network/Flask app context |
| **integration** | Tests interaction between 2–3 components; may use real DB or Flask test client; no full pipeline |
| **functional** | Tests a complete user-facing flow end-to-end; uses Flask test client + real routes + real DB |

**Naming convention for split files:**
- Integration-focused file → `test_<name>.py`
- Unit-focused companion → `test_<name>_unit.py`

**Path mirroring rule:** Every test file must mirror its `src/main_app/` counterpart:
- `src/main_app/db/db_Jobs.py` → `tests/unit/main_app/db/test_db_Jobs.py`
- `src/main_app/app_routes/auth/routes.py` → `tests/integration/main_app/app_routes/auth/test_routes.py`

